      "content": "That sense of being trapped in an inevitable glitch is incredibly heavy, and it makes perfect sense that small moments feel useless when they don't seem to stop the inevitable crash. It's not that you're failing to break the cycle, but rather that your brain is wired to see the final collapse, which can create a desperate rush to \"fix\" things before the inevitable drop happens. Since trying to control the outcome feels impossible, maybe the goal isn't to find a permanent solution, but to simply endure the next moment without fighting the feeling of inevitability.",
